user: What exactly is kosher food? 
system: Kosher food is a bunch of dietary rules that govern what a Jewish person is allowed to eat. 
user: Does it restrict the types of meat? 
system: Yes, certain types of animals and fishes are kosher. The method of killing is also quite important. 
user: Oh I see. Is it tasty? I want to try some. 
system: Well, there are many delicacies which are still considered kosher, so kosher doesn't mean more tasty or less tasty. 